      • onStopped

        public boolean onStopped()
        Description copied from interface: IPlugin
        Life-cycle of Plugin: ##### Step 4 STOP #####
        The Plugin is stopped --> it has to guarantee to leave its run-method as quick as possible:
        1. Use Plugin.isQuitRequested() to check if the run-method should be left. Or
        2. Set your own internal flag if IPlugin.onStopped() is called and check this flag in the Plugins run-method.

      • getLineFilter

        public java.util.regex.Pattern getLineFilter()
        Description copied from interface: ILogStreamDataListener
        This method should return a Pattern. This Pattern (regular expression) is used to filter the lines of the LogStream /log-file. Only for lines matching this expression the method ILogStreamDataListener.onNewLine(LogLine) or ILogStreamDataListener.onNewBlockOfLines(List) is called providing the matching line of the log-file.
        Returns:
